<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1156,350,480]" box="[160,409,350,376]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,409,350,376]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">External morphology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1156,350,480]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Shell external, translucent, background colour light brown to grey with dark brown, white and orange punctuations surrounded by small dark red points. Parapodia lighter in colour. Head lighter in colour, area around eyes pigmented.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="270" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,525,655]" box="[160,252,525,551]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,252,525,551]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Ecology</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1155,525,655]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Specimens were found crawling on calcareous rocks with green algae of undetermined species during night samplings. Egg masses were observed in November and juveniles in 
<date box="[160,340,630,655]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" value="2017-12">December 2017</date>
. Egg masses elongated, forming a ‘C’, with white eggs (
<figureCitation box="[969,1055,630,655]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[159,224,942,965]" captionTargetBox="[167,1146,148,918]" captionTargetId="figure-175@2.[162,1152,143,924]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. Distribution map of the western Mediterranean coast showing the main sampling stations. There should be only one image, currently there is a duplicate" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6758440" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6758440/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(c)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="270" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1156,699,829]" box="[160,300,699,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,300,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">Distribution</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[160,1156,699,829]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270">
Azores, Atlantic Spanish coast: Canary Islands; Mediterranean Spanish coast: Andalucía, Levantine coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Cervera JL &amp; Calado G &amp; Gavaia C &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Templado J &amp; Ballesteros M &amp; Megina C &amp; Garcia-Gomez JC" box="[351,565,769,794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" pagination="5 - 111" refId="ref18631" refString="Cervera JL, Calado G, Gavaia C, Malaquias MAE, Templado J, Ballesteros M, Megina C, Garcia-Gomez JC. 2004. An annotated and updated checklist of the opisthobranchs (Mollusca: Gastropoda) from Spain and Portugal (including Islands and archipelagos). Boletin-Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia. 20: 5 - 111." type="journal article" year="2004">Cervera et al. 2004</bibRefCitation>
), Catalonia (this study); Mediterranean French coast (
<bibRefCitation author="Garabedian K &amp; Malaquias MAE &amp; Crocetta F &amp; Zenetos A &amp; Kavadas S &amp; Valdes A" box="[166,421,804,829]" pageId="5" pageNumber="270" pagination="107 - 113" refId="ref19554" refString="Garabedian K, Malaquias MAE, Crocetta F, Zenetos A, Kavadas S, Valdes A. 2017. Haminoea orteai Talavera, Murillo and Templado, 1987 (Mollusca: Gastropoda: Heterobranchia: Cephalaspidea), a widespread species in the Mediterranean and northeastern Atlantic. Cah Biol Mar. 58: 107 - 113." type="journal article" year="2017">Garabedian et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
; this study); 
